<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Curer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I recently had a player I was grouped with mentioned how a cleric he was grouped with used a spell on a mob which kept the mob immobilized for 20 sec or so.  Anybody have any idea the name of this spell.  I think its Atone, but haven't been able to prove it yet.  After casting on mob, it appears as if the mob is slowing down, but hard to be sure.<P>At lvl 60, I have just started appreciating the spell Atone.  I didn't realize it was a blur spell.  I thought it was like all the other lull spells - never worked consistently.  Atone rocks..<g><P>------------------<BR>The Curer Saves....<BR>60 years <BR>Dark High Priest of Innoruuk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cali</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Clerics do not get a slow spell.  Neither slow as in run speed ala snare nor slow as in attack speed ala Turgxx.<P>Atone does a memory blur, though not always sucessful.  Effectively wiping the hate list.  The reason they may appear to "slow down" is that the mob has to regain agro.  So if your almost out of agro range they stop and look around a second (may appear slow ala snare) or it may take a minute to gain agro of a person hitting it (ala turgurs).<P>I find it effective when it works.  Though its a pain to try to use when in to close of quarters.  Really the only time I use it is to get by mobs in dungeons and thus I have trouble with it.  Either I cant get far enough away to have them NOT reagro on me or I cant see my target.   Frustrating to say the least.  Its a spell I rarely mem.<P>------------------<BR><B>~Calimayrn Anam'Cara</B><BR>Templar of Tunare<BR><B>~Calizana Rhinelander</B><BR>Floating Barbarian Champion<BR>Farstorm ~ Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Atone<BR>Wipe Hate List<BR>Classes: Clr (L34)<BR>Skill: Alteration<BR>Allowable Targets: All<BR>Range to Target: 200 feet<BR>Resistance Check: Magic + 25<BR>Mana Required: 60<BR>Spell Duration: Instant<BR>Casting Time: 4.50 seconds<BR>Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<BR>Recast Delay: 12.0 seconds<BR>Spell cast on you: You feel forgiveness in your mind.<BR>Spell cast on someone: Soandso calms down.<P>While the spdat file doesn't reveal every facet of a spell, one game mechanic that's pretty fundamental is that any debuff with a duration will eventually give a "Your (name) spell has ended."<P>Pretty safe to say that atone does not have any lasting effect on the mob.  I've atoned many mobs while passing through FM in earlier days and hunted in the zone for hours and never saw an atone wear off.  A good test to be sure of this is to atone a mob and then dispel it several times.  If it is a debuff it'll say that it wore off when it's dispelled.<P>What they probably saw was the mob lost aggro, and it took a few seconds for it to regain aggro.  (20 seconds is a very long time tho, sure it was kos to that group?)  In a fight situation, atone acting this way would have the same effect.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eyenea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have a cleric and an enchanter, and in my experience, the Atone series has been just as effective for my cleric as the memory blur series for enchanters.  Never had it wear off, although I think once or twice I had to cast Atone several times for the mob to forget me 8)<BR>Very nice for travelling 8)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">And with a Water Sprinkler of the Forgiven, ya don't even need to mem it =)<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 52nd Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) Master Tailor (161)<BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arele Nyxx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I carry an atone staff at all times.  Mostly I have to break it out when someone aggros a mob accidentally during a raid or whatnot.  The time to cast the staff is longer than the actual spell, but if you add in refresh time on the spell (none for staff) staff is quicker.  Atone isn't a spell that would wear off, it just clears the hate list...and yes, it doesn't always work on first cast...just keep clicking the staff until desired result is obtained.  <P>Also works great when someone is in dire need of a heal, but you don't want the faction hit on the mob they are killing.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.afterlifeguild.org/members.cgi?page=details&character=Arele" TARGET=_blank>Arele Nyxx</A> - <BR><A HREF="http://www.afterlifeguild.org" TARGET=_blank>Afterlife</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hehe, forgot about that faction thing Arele-though I used it for just that this last weekend in Chardok when I was battle-rezzing people after the Queen got loose early. It's interesting being the non-KOS cleric sometimes...<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 52nd Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) Master Tailor (161)<BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">naxy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Non-KOS in Chardok.<P>How much effort does it take to become Non-KOS in Chardok? Does it apply to all the mobs in the whole of Chardok?<P>Thanks!<P>------------------<BR>Naxy Dent, Vicar of Oasis Covenant on Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Belhaven</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Curer:<BR><B>I recently had a player I was grouped with mentioned how a cleric he was grouped with used a spell on a mob which kept the mob immobilized for 20 sec or so.  Anybody have any idea the name of this spell.  </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I'm guess he did one of two things:<P>Root the mob and then atone it - if you're away from it when root wears off, it may just stand there for a while.<P>Stun-lock it - continuously cast stuns on it in sequence to keep it where it was. <P><BR>Come to think of it - if it was just rooted out of melee range (root, immobilize, paralyzing earth) it would appear "immobilized".  <P>Atone, by itself, won't stop a mob.  After you cast it, even if it works, if you're in aggro range the mob will come after you again.<BR><p>[This message has been edited by Belhaven (edited 01-23-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Holyan Lightwalker</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stun Command is ~20 seconds of stun. It is an amazing spell.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've never had stun command last 20 seconds. More like 7. It's a targetable AoE though. And I have managed to stun myself a few times with it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stun command lasts 8 seconds.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
